File: eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede was placed on 30 days leave because of fraud and corruption charges she's facing. DURBAN - A decision is expected on Wednesday on whether eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede, will be allowed back at work. Gumede's 30-day leave of absence ended on Tuesday. She is facing fraud and corruption charges and is out on R50, 000 bail. READ: 'Poisoned eThekwini mayor: 'I am much stronger than before' Gumede will return to court on 8 August. The ANC hasn't yet decided on her fate, which means her leave may be extended until the matter is finalised. Meanwhile, the DA is calling for the eThekwini Metro to be put under administration and to be dissolved.